    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "text": "Curved streets and Tudor‑style buildings define Forest Hills Gardens, the neighborhood’s planned community.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        7
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 1"
      ],
      "source": "https://www.nyc.gov/site/queenscb6/about/forest-hills.page"
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "text": "Austin Street has become Queens’ premier shopping and dining strip, hosting Eddie’s Sweet Shop since 1925 alongside modern cafés.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        8
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 2"
      ],
      "source": "https://www.cityneighborhoods.nyc/forest-hills"
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "text": "The Long Island Rail Road opened a Forest Hills station in 1906, followed by the Queens Boulevard trolley seven years later.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
